The paper deals with coding schemes for relay channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The use of LDPC codes is a common technique in coding theory and communications, which suggests the paper could also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) and computer communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories.
